<p>Easy one, but I can't find an answer.</p>  <p>I wanna to list sub-categories to create tabs in code below. This one works fine in my output. But the first tab needs a <code>&lt;li class= "selected" &gt;</code> to show the content on page load .</p>  <p>How to force the first echo result to include a class on <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element ?</p>  <p>.</p>  <p>.</p>  <p>.</p>  <p>[ Output ]</p>  <p>Actual: .......... Category 1 | Category 2 | Category 3</p>  <p>Needed: .......... Category 1* | Category 2 | Category 3</p>  <p>*class="selected"</p>  <pre><code>  &lt;ul class="cd-tabs-navigation"&gt;    &lt;?php   $argumentos = array(   'hide_empty' =&gt; 1,   'child_of' =&gt; 44,   );   $categories = get_categories($argumentos);   foreach($categories as $category) {   echo '&lt;li&gt;&lt;a data-content="' . $category-&gt;slug . '" href="#' . $category-&gt;slug . '"&gt;' . $category-&gt;name . '&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;';   }   ?&gt;    &lt;/ul&gt; </code></pre>  <p>.</p>  <p>.</p>  <p>[ EDIT ]</p>  <p>The solution by Lal. Thank you everyone!</p>  <pre><code>  foreach($categories as $category) {   if(++$i==1)   echo '&lt;li class="selected"&gt;&lt;a class="selected" data-content="' . $category-&gt;slug . '" href="#' . $category-&gt;slug . '"&gt;' . $category-&gt;name . '&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;';   else   echo '&lt;li&gt;&lt;a data-content="' . $category-&gt;slug . '" href="#' . $category-&gt;slug . '"&gt;' . $category-&gt;name . '&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;';   } </code></pre>